BRAZIL DAYBOOK: Current Account, Central Government Budget

-- B y   H e l d e r   M a r i n h o
-- 
2011-04-26T03:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-26/brazil-daybook-current-account-central-government-budget.html
Brazil ’s current account deficit
probably widened to $4.8 billion in March from $3.39 billion in
February, according to the median estimate in a Bloomberg survey
of 19 economists. The gap will rise to $60 billion this year,
from $47.5 billion last year, as companies increase profit
remittances and Brazilians boost imports and trips abroad, the
central bank estimates. The bank releases figures for the month
of March at 10:30 a.m. local time.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Cia. Paranaense de Energia hosts meeting with investors in Rio
de Janeiro at 8:30 a.m.
*BM&FBovespa SA’s Chief Executive Officer Edemir Pinto speaks to
reporters in Sao Paulo about initial public offerings in Brazil,
at 9 a.m.
*Usiminas Chief Executive Officer Wilson Brumer and  Rio de
Janeiro ’s Governor Sergio Cabral hold news conference on the
environmental recovery of the Inga Mercantil Area, at 10 a.m.
*Gerdau SA holds shareholder meeting in  Porto Alegre .
*Treasury Secretary Arno Augustin speaks to reporters in
Brasilia about the central government budget balance in the
month of March at 12 p.m.
*The Treasury auctions inflation-linked bonds NTN-B; results
will be announced at 2:30 p.m.  ECONOMY: *FGV construction costs at 8 a.m.
*March current account at 10:30 a.m.
*March foreign direct investment at 10:30 a.m.
*March Central Government budget balance at 11:30 a.m.  EQUITIES:
*Fibria (FIBR3 BZ) gained the most in a month on pulp price
outlook
*Toyota Mercosul (7203 JP) will halt production at a Brazilian
plant on April 25, May 6 and May 20 on consequences from the
Japan tsunami
*Banco do Brasil (BBAS3 BZ) plans to boost gains from
international brances to 9 percent of total profit
*HRT (HRTP3 BZ) started drilling its first well in the Amazon
region  MARKETS
*The Bovespa index fell 0.1 percent to 66,972.37.
